parts.body: Watch the 2024-2025 Membership Video   August 13, 2024     Be the One: Watch the 2024-2025 Membership Video   When you join DECA, you're not just another member; you're part of a global network of emerging leaders and entrepreneurs who are shaping the future. Check out DECA's 2024-2025 membership video to help your chapter show students why joining DECA empowers members to Be The One who makes a difference in the world. WATCH NOW   DECA NEWS   One DECA Call Tonight Join the Executive Officer team for the first One DECA Call of the year tonight at 8:30 PM ET / 5:30 PM ET. LEARN MORE 2024-2025 DECA Conference Lineup DECA has a full lineup of educational conferences for its members. Check out where we're heading next! LEARN MORE Taking Stocks with Teens Survey Share what's trending by taking the 2024 Fall Piper Sandler Taking Stock With Teens Survey! LEARN MORE Program of Leadership DECA’s Executive Officer team is excited to introduce this year’s program of leadership. LEARN MORE Check out the Brand Center Visit the updated Brand Resource Center for resources to boost your chapter's recruitment efforts. LEARN MORE 2024-2025 DECA Guide The 2024-2025 DECA Guide provides all the information you need to have a successful year. Watch the 2024-2025 Membership Video
 

August 13, 2024
 
 

Be the One: Watch the 2024-2025 Membership Video

 

When you join DECA, you're not just another member; you're part of a global network of emerging leaders and entrepreneurs who are shaping the future. Check out DECA's 2024-2025 membership video to help your chapter show students why joining DECA empowers members to Be The One who makes a difference in the world.
WATCH NOW
 

DECA NEWS
 

One DECA Call Tonight


Join the Executive Officer team for the first One DECA Call of the year tonight at 8:30 PM ET / 5:30 PM ET.
LEARN MORE

2024-2025 DECA Conference Lineup


DECA has a full lineup of educational conferences for its members. Check out where we're heading next!
LEARN MORE

Taking Stocks with Teens Survey


Share what's trending by taking the 2024 Fall Piper Sandler Taking Stock With Teens Survey!
LEARN MORE

Program of Leadership


DECA’s Executive Officer team is excited to introduce this year’s program of leadership.
LEARN MORE

Check out the Brand Center


Visit the updated Brand Resource Center for resources to boost your chapter's recruitment efforts.
LEARN MORE

2024-2025 DECA Guide


The 2024-2025 DECA Guide provides all the information you need to have a successful year.
DOWNLOAD NOW

EXECUTIVE OFFICER CORNER
 

Recruit, Retain, Repeat: Strategies for Maintaining Chapter Memberships


DECA is poised to reach record membership levels yet again. Establishing a strong support framework is crucial to maintaining this growth and effectively nurturing new chapters. Here is how you can foster retention and create a lasting impact.


by Fatimah Naraghi | Central Region Division President
LEARN MORE

START YOUR YEAR
 

Fighting a Dupe


Step into the role of the owner of Heart Rate, an affordable brand of athletic wear. Your business partner wants you to determine whether or not to offer a new product as a “dupe” of a more expensive luxury brand.

headers.Subject: Reminder: Visit Pacific in August and we’ll waive your application fee!

parts.body:
Personalized tours built for you and your interests

                              New England Campus; California Vibe




Visit Pacific in August and we'll waive your application fee!




                                If you're looking for an ivy-covered collegiate campus with laidback, West Coast energy, check out University of the Pacific, Varadan. We'd love for you to schedule a visit! Our tours are guided by students who can't wait to show you their favorite spots on Pacific's historical campus.                              





                                And as a bonus: If you visit the campus in August, we'll waive the $55 application fee when you apply for admission through the Pacific application within seven days of your visit!                              





Schedule a Tour <https://connect.pacific.edu/portal/undergradvisit?utm_source=Slate&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=APP+FEE+WAIVE&utm_id=visit&utm_content=1>



                                We can't wait to see you on campus.                               





Go Tigers!🐾





Chris Ferguson

Vice President, Enrollment Strategy
                                University of the Pacific





 




Stay Informed About Pacific News & Events
Follow Us on Social Media




 




Have admissions questions?

admission@pacific.edu

                                209.946.2211                              



University of the Pacific

                                3601 Pacific Avenue                              

                                Stockton, CA 95211

headers.Subject: Tufts Students Answer "Why Tufts?"

parts.body:
Hi Varadan,

      As you wade into the college search waters, be sure to ask yourself what you want and need in your college experience.

      While you reflect on what you're looking for, current college students may provide some helpful insights. At Tufts, there are many ways to find student voices to learn more about their experiences in the community. Here's where we suggest you start:

	 JUMBO Magazine <https://admissions.tufts.edu/discover-tufts/jumbo-magazine/> -- in each issue, we ask current students our favorite question --  "Why Tufts?" Read the answer from Jed Quiaoit '25 in our latest issue.
	 Jumbo Talk <http://admissions.tufts.edu/blogs/> -- our blogs! We have a dedicated team of bloggers who are eager to share their Tufts experiences with prospective students. 
	 Hear from current students <https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLVUoO64HX951UCTyuxkyGneqdl1VWxaya> -- Tufts is filled with kind students, all of whom are eager to share their journey with academic exploration and finding their fit.

If you have any questions along the way, we're here to help!

    All our best, 
    Tufts Admissions

Tufts is a medium-sized research and liberal arts university of 6,000+ undergraduate students, located in the greater Boston area. We encourage close student-faculty relationships, foster a culture of research and innovation, and celebrate the diverse experiences of our students, who are known for being kind, intellectually playful, down-to-earth, driven, collaborative, and civically-minded. Our students enroll in one of three schools: the School of Arts and Sciences, the School of Engineering, or the School of the Museum of Fine Arts (SMFA). Tufts proudly meets 100% of the demonstrated financial need of all admitted students, regardless of citizenship status.


This email was sent to vk6878@pleasantonusd.net by Tufts Admissions.

parts.body:
Full scholarships to QuestBridge college partners |

 







Dear Varadan,
                                                               

Did you know that top colleges are actively seeking high-achieving students from low-income backgrounds? Through the 2024 National College Match <https://www.questbridge.org/apply-to-college/programs/national-college-match?utm_campaign=CMrecruitment_drip&utm_content=re073&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Slate>, you can apply for free to our college partners and be considered for a full four-year scholarship. Learn more about the program <https://www.questbridge.org/apply-to-college/programs/national-college-match/apply?utm_campaign=CMrecruitment_drip&utm_content=re073&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Slate> and apply by Thursday, September 26, 2024.









Full four-year scholarships to over 50 top colleges


                                QuestBridge's 52 college partners <https://www.questbridge.org/partners/college-partners?utm_campaign=CMrecruitment_drip&utm_content=re073&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Slate> are committed to making college affordable — and even free — for students who excel academically despite financial hardship, and they partner with us to find these students. Some of our college partners include:                              









Apply now <https://apply.questbridge.org/portal/apply?utm_campaign=CMrecruitment_drip&utm_content=re073&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Slate>







                                Over 14,000 students have received full four-year scholarships through the National College Match. These students dared to dream big, and so can you. Start your application today <https://apply.questbridge.org/portal/apply?utm_campaign=CMrecruitment_drip&utm_content=re073&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Slate>.

                                We look forward to reviewing your application!

                                Kind regards,                              









                                Ana Rowena Mallari                              

                                QuestBridge Co-Founder and CEO                              









Learn more about QuestBridge








Watch videos about our college partners → <https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLjMa1kvfkoLhM2OhNZBnOJ2vHkeOsDOhx&utm_campaign=CMrecruitment_drip&utm_content=re073&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Slate>






Learn more about who is eligible to apply → <https://www.questbridge.org/apply-to-college/programs/national-college-match/apply?utm_campaign=CMrecruitment_drip&utm_content=re073&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Slate>






Explore materials in our Resource Library → <https://www.questbridge.org/apply-to-college/resources?resourceAudience&utm_campaign=CMrecruitment_drip&utm_content=re073&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Slate[0]=12&resourceTopic[0]=applying>









Have a question? Visit AskQB → <https://questbridge.zendesk.com/hc/en-us?utm_campaign=CMrecruitment_drip&utm_content=re073&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Slate>



QuestBridge | PO Box 51847, Palo Alto, CA 94303

QuestBridge is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization.

Full scholarships to QuestBridge college partners |
 

Dear Varadan,
 

Did you know that top colleges are actively seeking high-achieving students from low-income backgrounds? Through the 2024 National College Match, you can apply for free to our college partners and be considered for a full four-year scholarship. Learn more about the program and apply by Thursday, September 26, 2024.

Full four-year scholarships to over 50 top colleges

QuestBridge's 52 college partners are committed to making college affordable — and even free — for students who excel academically despite financial hardship, and they partner with us to find these students. Some of our college partners include:

Apply now

Over 14,000 students have received full four-year scholarships through the National College Match. These students dared to dream big, and so can you. Start your application today.

We look forward to reviewing your application!

Kind regards,

Ana Rowena Mallari

QuestBridge Co-Founder and CEO

Learn more about QuestBridge

Watch videos about our college partners →

Learn more about who is eligible to apply →

Explore materials in our Resource Library →

Have a question? Visit AskQB →

QuestBridge | PO Box 51847, Palo Alto, CA 94303

headers.Subject: There’s No Better Time to Become a Husker

parts.body:
UNIVERSITY of NEBRASKA-LINCOLN

Varadan,

As you begin your college search process, we want to fill you in on what the University of Nebraska–Lincoln is doing to support you this application season. There is no place like Nebraska, and there is no better time to become a Husker!

Nebraska is test-optional for admission and test-preferred for full scholarship consideration. We encourage students to take the ACT/SAT and submit their test score to maximize scholarship consideration.

Important Dates & Deadlines »

Admission Requirements »

Apply to Nebraska »=> https://admissions.unl.edu/apply/
Visit Campus

The best way to get a preview of all you can accomplish at Nebraska is to experience it for yourself! During your visit, you'll tour campus with a current Nebraska student as your guide and learn more about student involvement opportunities and important admission, scholarship and financial aid information.

Visit Options

Husker Weekdays are available Monday-Friday. This option allows you to tour campus with a current student and meet with a representative from the college of your choice.  

Red Letter Days allow students to tour campus with a current student, eat lunch in a dining center, learn about engagement opportunities and explore resources for success.


	September 13
	October 11
	October 18
	November 1
	November 15


Virtual Visit Week

Attend any of our Virtual Visit Week webinars from September 24–26 to learn about important admissions topics! We'll have sessions for in- and out-of-state scholarships, financial aid and academic sessions with various colleges and the University Honors program. 

Register Now »

The Cornhusker Connection

Join us for The Cornhusker Connection event on Friday, October 4! This half-day visit during Nebraska's homecoming week allows you to visit college open houses, tour the campus, and browse a "Get to Know You" fair featuring various organizations, offices, and college representatives.

Register Now »

Pre-Health at Nebraska

Register for Nebraska's Pre-Health event Monday, October 7! This is a can't-miss opportunity for high school students who are seeking a career in the healthcare field to learn more about what Nebraska has to offer, specific program information and how to prepare for success. 

Register Now »

Plan Your Next Visit »=> https://admissions.unl.edu/visit/
Discover Your Path

Start by making a list of your favorite hobbies and school subjects, then talk to your teachers and counselors about how you can pursue these passions in a career. 

At Nebraska, you'll find the support to create your future as you study what you love.

If you're unsure what to major in, you can apply without choosing. Once you're on campus, the Explore Center will pair you with a professional advisor who will help you identify your interests, skills and values to assist with choosing a major that's right for you.



Explore 100+ Majors »=> https://go.unl.edu/majors
There is no place like Nebraska, and there is no better time for you to be a Husker! If you have any questions, please contact the Office of Admissions at admissions@unl.edu or 402-472-2023.

Clearthur Mangram
Director of Admissions
Office of Admissions
University of Nebraska-Lincoln

headers.Subject: Your Guide to Brown: Meet Brown University

parts.body:
Distinct for its student-centered learning and deep sense of purpose

Meet Brown University

Brown's innovative Open Curriculum, with no core requirements outside of your concentration, makes you the architect of your own education. This flexible, rigorous approach to the undergraduate experience encourages students to be creative thinkers, intellectual risk-takers and entrepreneurial problem-solvers.

If this purposeful approach to education intrigues you, know that we are here to assist you through your college search process and encourage you to learn more about Brown through our online resources:

	 For more information about the Open Curriculum <https://www.brown.edu/academics/undergraduate/open-curriculum>, applying <http://admission.brown.edu/apply> to Brown, or financial aid <http://admission.brown.edu/tuition-aid>, we invite you to visit the Undergraduate Admission <http://admission.brown.edu/> website.


	 An education at Brown is more affordable than you think. Our Quick College Cost Estimator <http://app.myintuitionapp.org/institution/35aa3353-a90e-4d01-b708-176c38f878f8/costestimator> tool can help you anticipate your college costs and estimate your eligibility for need-based scholarships.


	 Engage with the Brown community online <https://admission.brown.edu/visit>, including a virtual campus tour, or visit us in Providence and take an in-person campus tour <https://admission.brown.edu/visit/campus-tours-0>.


	 Reach out to current Brown students <mailto:askastudent@brown.edu> with any questions.


	 Follow us on Instagram <http://www.instagram.com/brownuadmission/> and Facebook <http://www.facebook.com/brownadmission/>.
 



Learn more <https://www.brown.edu/>   Visit our campus <https://admission.brown.edu/visit>
 

Office of Admission <https://admission.brown.edu/>
401-863-2378 | admission@brown.edu
Take a Virtual Tour of Campus <https://www.brown.edu/admission/undergraduate/#virtualtour>
Questions about life at Brown? | Ask a Brown Student! <mailto:askastudent@brown.edu>

Meet Brown University

Brown's innovative Open Curriculum, with no core requirements outside of your concentration, makes you the architect of your own education. This flexible, rigorous approach to the undergraduate experience encourages students to be creative thinkers, intellectual risk-takers and entrepreneurial problem-solvers.

If this purposeful approach to education intrigues you, know that we are here to assist you through your college search process and encourage you to learn more about Brown through our online resources:

  • For more information about the Open Curriculum, applying to Brown, or financial aid, we invite you to visit the Undergraduate Admission website.

  • An education at Brown is more affordable than you think. Our Quick College Cost Estimator tool can help you anticipate your college costs and estimate your eligibility for need-based scholarships.

  • Engage with the Brown community online, including a virtual campus tour, or visit us in Providence and take an in-person campus tour.

  • Reach out to current Brown students with any questions.

  • Follow us on Instagram and Facebook.

headers.Subject: NSHSS Lifetime of Benefits

parts.body:
A membership that keeps on giving 
National Society of High School Scholars | 
NSHSS | View Online
 
A welcome from an NSHSS Fellows Board Trustee
Kolby Keo, Director of International Affairs at FGS Globaland president emeritus of Young Professionals in Foreign Policy (YPFP), shares his experience as an NSHSS lifetime member.
A Membership That Keeps on Giving
 Today, more than ever, its important to celebrate good news. And thats what this moment isI congratulate you on your invitation to NSHSS! Youve been invited to join a network of accomplished peers who are tomorrows leaders, leading today.When I first got my NSHSS invitation, I wont lie, I was skeptical. What could this group do for me? I took the dive and became a member my junior year in 2008. But even so, I didnt do much with my membership. There was a whole range of programs and benefits I never looked into, and to this day I regret not getting involved earlier. But heres where my NSHSS story gets interesting.It wasnt until seven years later, after graduating high school, attending three different colleges (a story for another time), earning my political science degree at UC Irvine (the first in my family to complete college), and moving across the country to start my first full-time job that I truly realized the lifetime benefits of being an NSHSS member.NSHSS was seeking applicants to join the executive board of theNSHSS Fellows Program. Fellows are NSHSS alumni members who are interested in remaining involved with the organization and working to better themselves and their communities. Three interviews later I was welcomed as board vice president. And after several years with NSHSS Fellows, Ive helped organize dozens of member events, taken the stage in front of thousands, advised NSHSS leaders on the future of the organization, and met and learned from so many brilliant scholars.Ive also sat at the table with corporate CEOs, senior government leaders, and education and nonprofit executivesall thanks to NSHSS. And the great thing is, that as an NSHSS member, you get to meet and engage with these top professionals too.The NSHSS Fellows board members have become my close friends. Though were spread throughout the country, welook out for each other. We lift each other up. And we continually challenge each other to do and be better. With NSHSS, Ive found an invaluable personal and professional community.What these years have proved to me, even after getting involved late in the game, is that NSHSS truly offers a *lifetime* membership. I sincerely hope you decide to be part of our community, and once you join, I emphatically encourage you to take full advantage of your membership. Attend the events, apply for all the scholarships, engage on social media, join a leadership program, find and use your voice, and really take the time to meet and befriend your fellow members.Be safe, be well, and I hope to see you at future NSHSS programs.Cheers,Kolby KeoPacifica High School, Class of 2010University of California, Irvine, Class of 2015Trustee of the NSHSS Fellows Leadership Program

A membership that keeps on giving
              
National Society of High School Scholars  |   NSHSS  |  View Online
  

A welcome from an NSHSS Fellows Board Trustee

Kolby Keo, Director of International Affairs at FGS Global and president emeritus of Young Professionals in Foreign Policy (YPFP), shares his experience as an NSHSS lifetime member.

A Membership That Keeps on Giving

Today, more than ever, it’s important to celebrate good news. And that’s what this moment is—I congratulate you on your invitation to NSHSS! You’ve been invited to join a network of accomplished peers who are tomorrow’s leaders, leading today.  

When I first got my NSHSS invitation, I won’t lie, I was skeptical. What could this group do for me? I took the dive and became a member my junior year in 2008. But even so, I didn’t do much with my membership. There was a whole range of programs and benefits I never looked into, and to this day I regret not getting involved earlier. But here’s where my NSHSS story gets interesting.

It wasn’t until seven years later, after graduating high school, attending three different colleges (a story for another time), earning my political science degree at UC Irvine (the first in my family to complete college), and moving across the country to start my first full-time job that I truly realized the lifetime benefits of being an NSHSS member.

NSHSS was seeking applicants to join the executive board of the NSHSS Fellows Program. Fellows are NSHSS alumni members who are interested in remaining involved with the organization and working to better themselves and their communities. Three interviews later I was welcomed as board vice president. And after several years with NSHSS Fellows, I’ve helped organize dozens of member events, taken the stage in front of thousands, advised NSHSS leaders on the future of the organization, and met and learned from so many brilliant scholars.  

I’ve also sat at the table with corporate CEOs, senior government leaders, and education and nonprofit executives—all thanks to NSHSS. And the great thing is, that as an NSHSS member, you get to meet and engage with these top professionals too.

The NSHSS Fellows board members have become my close friends. Though we’re spread throughout the country, we look out for each other. We lift each other up. And we continually challenge each other to do and be better. With NSHSS, I’ve found an invaluable personal and professional community.

What these years have proved to me, even after getting involved late in the game, is that NSHSS truly offers a *lifetime* membership. I sincerely hope you decide to be part of our community, and once you join, I emphatically encourage you to take full advantage of your membership. Attend the events, apply for all the scholarships, engage on social media, join a leadership program, find and use your voice, and really take the time to meet and befriend your fellow members.

Be safe, be well, and I hope to see you at future NSHSS programs.

Cheers,
Kolby Keo
Pacifica High School, Class of 2010
University of California, Irvine, Class of 2015
Trustee of the NSHSS Fellows Leadership Program

headers.Subject: Explore Our Home From Yours

parts.body:
Take a Virtual Tour

Undergraduate Admissions <https://admissions.ncsu.edu?utm_campaign=junior-prospects&utm_content=virtual-tour&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate&utm_term=2020>

                    Walk the Bricks                  


                    Hi Varadan,                  

                    From the grassy lawn of the Court of North Carolina, to the red bricks of our iconic Brickyard and Hunt Library, the library of the future - you can experience it all before stepping on campus.                  

                    Take our virtual tour to see what it's like to live and learn as part of the Wolfpack.                  

Take a Tour <https://bit.ly/3FOM0BY?utm_campaign=junior-prospects&utm_content=virtual-tour&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate&utm_term=2020>


                            Talley
                            Student Union                          

                            The heart of all student life. Where you can enjoy a coffee, stake out a study spot, grab a meal between classes or spend time in the various student support centers.                          

Tour Talley Student Union <https://bit.ly/3pN8M7R?utm_campaign=junior-prospects&utm_content=virtual-tour&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate&utm_term=2020>




                            Court of North Carolina                          

                            Study or relax on the grassy lawn on a sunny day or enjoy class outside. Lined with some of the oldest buildings on campus, this area is where you will take many first-year classes.                          

Browse the Court of North Carolina <https://bit.ly/31mcLie?utm_campaign=junior-prospects&utm_content=virtual-tour&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate&utm_term=2020>




                            James B. Hunt Jr. Library                          

                            Dubbed the Library of the Future, Hunt Library was built to provide unique and collaborative study spaces for students and researchers. Prep for your next exam in one of the hundreds of study spaces, find a comfy chair for reading or record your own music in a Music Production Room.                          

Experience Hunt Library <https://bit.ly/3pLVick?utm_campaign=junior-prospects&utm_content=virtual-tour&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate&utm_term=2020>




                            University Housing                          

                            Residential life helps you grow both academically and personally. With 20 different residence halls across campus, you'll be close to classes, dining and the gym.                          

Explore University Housing <https://bit.ly/3FPgnIA?utm_campaign=junior-prospects&utm_content=virtual-tour&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate&utm_term=2020>





NC State University <https://www.ncsu.edu?utm_campaign=junior-prospects&utm_content=virtual-tour&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate&utm_term=2020>

parts.body:
When you come to Chicago, you'll feel it 🌆

        VARADAN, CHICAGO IS READY...      

                                ...TO BE YOUR HOME                              


Not every alum of DePaul University ends up writing a viral hit about Chicago <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EoVQ_TQFJy0>, but when you join our Blue Demon community... you'll feel it.

With over 125,000 working alumni in the Chicago area, you've got a network of professionals, artists, entrepreneurs, changemakers, and friendly faces waiting to meet you.

Coming here is just the beginning, Varadan.

parts.body:
We can’t wait to meet you – here’s info about USF!

Explore Life at USF //

Hey Varadan,

We’re so excited to tell you more about the University of South Florida. As a top 50 public U.S. university (https://programs.usf.edu/e3t/Ctc/DG+113/c2j-204/MVKSXZWs09xW4C07Z6748pJ_W5g6HvJ5jHPdhN6mkvpj5jGjMW69t95C6lZ3mtW4gCmTl72_-DMW1QWR1v43p9MNW4sHP1G8Q8C0pVxyKDK2stHBMVgTdv97wMJb2W1hf3__4zz0brW65jTBW4PKvQcN1jfpwpRKFyZW5KzHH35K_1nRW8GR3rv7xK0TRVvf4NY6qvjxRW5Cl9Jc4r8BngW2jTLNz2DCvJvW8DtDNR85BXrVW8V6tHp2rJ6SKW6zqyyL79DMcqW2kYNKH3d8_GfW6Ytgdf3SsryCW90d3s835p6ZKW1GnRq94-HHbMW4ZS1wH86LS5wW1YGc3F4CfcxyW4NL8tB6Cz438VtVQ9K3g7P4lW5bPpc92x3M8tW3hp9nG2bsjhRW52WLZH8nV92cW3QrQcK7DlJRNW2SmS_c8ktRR_VKHnNY6nTn0QV-KZrs6yW2GyN7bwD4FkwXnXW1HGtR21cJp9yW6r7dM24_TlkYW1wnWPF2msq8YW18cdfP1P9Xlkf4-d9Bl04 ) , we take your success seriously — both inside and outside the classroom.

We want to help you make incredible memories at USF that will last a lifetime. We encourage students to jump into campus life, offering:

- More than 600 student organizations
- Thousands of on-campus events across all three campuses (https://programs.usf.edu/e3t/Ctc/DG+113/c2j-204/MVKSXZWs09xW4C07Z6748pJ_W5g6HvJ5jHPdhN6mkvqb3l5QzW7Y8-PT6lZ3nhW4GRd432JpH3lW8S5jJv6HY0w3W38xL2L4G5nTXW4ZW8Cx3cKWjzW2m0rCz4SythsN7kX24QVJZYhV8pmZJ6frs1nW899zDR7d9s20W159VJ84b51RPW6Lsy2T2zJ9gPW8Q1bR_44N72KW40m0LQ3rt12GVs6t6X6mdyp5W3CtMCH4b6TYKW6Pr_vG2pvFG1W2X8x123N485KVqw5KM2_JKJ2W6zsjhG6FKt24W71jhdz440j9xW8dFWsV15zh7kW62-hBq4PxTBBVjjTMK60SZYgW8QFsH46w7FQmN2-0pkNZcRCLVXYP918NmDyyW8kkSTV60cRx4f76yfF804 )
- Free admission to all varsity sports events, including football

Life at USF is always exciting, but don’t take our word for it! See for yourself why USF is the place to live your best college life:

Watch: This is USF
(https://programs.usf.edu/e3t/Ctc/DG+113/c2j-204/MVKSXZWs09xW4C07Z6748pJ_W5g6HvJ5jHPdhN6mkvpC3l5QzW6N1vHY6lZ3mpN1CBx5lXq66zW8Zpc2F3znPz1W7MB7wG66FX8gW6G89Xs7HzL_WW3ZTjWw3x70PcW4g0-_C3mYrglW8WPDP95JZWSNW2X_2S04m_sJ4W5H8wqw1BB0XrW83yysk3kxSDNW1KF9181Ry8l_VkPh-_2tspYFW1px5lC8TjSKYN3HmM-Zx7mlKW7sK2nY6w9NyKW287Q3Y2B609BW3brYcb1vmVBhW16Y92s5zmshQN5PWHRPN99H5W8kKm7L3qCKRyW7vm74s77NMsrW9kvkNs2gL8-Vf1LkDw204 )

Video Thumbnail (https://programs.usf.edu/e3t/Ctc/DG+113/c2j-204/MVKSXZWs09xW4C07Z6748pJ_W5g6HvJ5jHPdhN6mkvpC3l5QzW6N1vHY6lZ3mpN1CBx5lXq66zW8Zpc2F3znPz1W7MB7wG66FX8gW6G89Xs7HzL_WW3ZTjWw3x70PcW4g0-_C3mYrglW8WPDP95JZWSNW2X_2S04m_sJ4W5H8wqw1BB0XrW83yysk3kxSDNW1KF9181Ry8l_VkPh-_2tspYFW1px5lC8TjSKYN3HmM-Zx7mlKW7sK2nY6w9NyKW287Q3Y2B609BW3brYcb1vmVBhW16Y92s5zmshQN5PWHRPN99H5W8kKm7L3qCKRyW7vm74s77NMsrW9kvkNs2gL8-Vf1LkDw204 )

Prestigious Academic Experience

Have you already discovered your lifelong passion, or are you unsure? If you’re still deciding, USF offers an Exploratory Curriculum to help you explore your options when you enroll.

Exploratory Curriculum
(https://programs.usf.edu/e3t/Ctc/DG+113/c2j-204/MVKSXZWs09xW4C07Z6748pJ_W5g6HvJ5jHPdhN6mkvpC3l5QzW6N1vHY6lZ3m_W5vQcD86L2fShN383m5L62_DZW6s4GBH1cr5y5N2_RrFmSxs2TW9hRd6r6K51FgN85MLvRr5NJ_W2Wq83G7yMvZrN6tG8DcTgnHBW3vFr2_2wszqDW4VyPjB6SWMHJVjY-GX32TLJ_W7YfJVB5Hcfk3Ms9cWL107-DN6mpwy3yM2zkW6f2d163qmZDhW49vFl66hshRXW3q2C5V51W3fPF2fD8c9ZH6CW35zMVr8-1MqXN2RHNFgY7QlkW11jRjd35-QyqW85lX7Y8Gtk3Mf4RLRfP04 )

200+ Majors and Concentrations

If you have decided on a major, know that USF offers around 200 majors and concentrations across all three campuses.

View All Majors
(https://programs.usf.edu/e3t/Ctc/DG+113/c2j-204/MVKSXZWs09xW4C07Z6748pJ_W5g6HvJ5jHPdhN6mkvpW3l5QzW7lCdLW6lZ3ldW7m6lly351qHHN3WyLX7rJYzKV2_Bpq57HXCQW1NNQmC5b-fxFVZV6hf2LxYq3W7S3BQr49zC0bV-DXY_1nn03sW7y-f617qGVlyW4h-k02183CVvN2jMJCJdRMSTN5_Wrw4vgWfTVGgfGF5NJw5-W5k2pvt55NJBQN82mkRCKYq99N8NfVndsrMw0W3v_KNk5r9wLgW5qWTb62pwb4SW1kgDm45xpfnNW6PTXyV3G1HbLW6j2lhC4w3NZYVZ8-N-2sSDN0W9kP1Jv30MlvfW2vbPKs45n1G4W2bL9Cp2jHBr0f1qbFVz04 )

Come Take a Campus Tour

Want to see yourself at USF? Take a tour of our three campuses!

-

USF Tampa - Our largest campus, USF Tampa, is in the heart of Uptown, an innovation district on the rise.

- USF St. Petersburg - USF St. Petersburg is our midsized campus, perfectly situated between the cultural hub of Downtown St. Petersburg and waterfront Bayboro Harbor.
- USF Sarasota-Manatee - Our smallest campus has a tight-knit student body and a faculty that’s on a first-name basis with them all.

Take a Campus Tour
(https://programs.usf.edu/e3t/Ctc/DG+113/c2j-204/MVKSXZWs09xW4C07Z6748pJ_W5g6HvJ5jHPdhN6mkvpC3l5QzW6N1vHY6lZ3pRVq4dG88NgdvRW7F58dB78SbVvW7B27ZX6JJQfGW8r2vyt3KS2vtW2fB0g31j1fbyW9dhSPN82z3Z7W2NCB0n48Sk69W7q0nQ223w4MBVRpkWr4ZP5R6W86TSpy93m3gLW22dCvS2k2lM4W35-s9d7QVZnmW1k-jx423tM8fW9k8CwK3X7f18W1t7gLT3zJvJPW8BMkHW4mpxjZW610RgK44R-jKV6wtQy31nYynVfH2K-56JjqNW4dWf0g5v2g1SW81wDJZ6WScVyW3X01C86HYkf0f4NckLb04 )

Ready to Apply?

We can’t wait to meet you – here’s info about USF!

Explore Life at USF //

Hey Varadan,

 

We’re so excited to tell you more about the University of South Florida. As a top 50 public U.S. university, we take your success seriously — both inside and outside the classroom.

 

We want to help you make incredible memories at USF that will last a lifetime. We encourage students to jump into campus life, offering:

  • More than 600 student organizations 
  • Thousands of on-campus events across all three campuses
  • Free admission to all varsity sports events, including football

Life at USF is always exciting, but don’t take our word for it! See for yourself why USF is the place to live your best college life:

Watch: This is USF

Prestigious Academic Experience

Have you already discovered your lifelong passion, or are you unsure? If you’re still deciding, USF offers an Exploratory Curriculum to help you explore your options when you enroll.
Exploratory Curriculum

200+ Majors and Concentrations

 

If you have decided on a major, know that USF offers around 200 majors and concentrations across all three campuses.

View All Majors

Come Take a Campus Tour

 

Want to see yourself at USF? Take a tour of our three campuses! 

  • USF Tampa - Our largest campus, USF Tampa, is in the heart of Uptown, an innovation district on the rise. 

  • USF St. Petersburg - USF St. Petersburg is our midsized campus, perfectly situated between the cultural hub of Downtown St. Petersburg and waterfront Bayboro Harbor. 
  • USF Sarasota-Manatee - Our smallest campus has a tight-knit student body and a faculty that’s on a first-name basis with them all.
Take a Campus Tour

Ready to Apply?

 

If you’re ready to apply, that’s fantastic. We can’t wait to get your application! We recommend applying as soon as possible so you have the best shot at getting your campus of choice, on-campus housing and more.
Apply Now

Rocky D. Bull

Admissions Recruiter Advisor

Pleasanton Unified School District posted in Pleasanton Unified School District, Undisclosed

We Want to Hear from You: Listening Campaign Coming Soon to Inform Hiring of the Next Superintendent

_Sent on behalf of Board President Mary Jo Carreon_​Dear PUSD community,​As an initial step in the process to hire the next superintendent of the Pleasanton Unified School District, the Board of Trustees seeks to engage the district’s educational partners (e.g., staff, families, community members) in a listening campaign to identify the desired professional and personal characteristics for the next superintendent.​

The Board would greatly appreciate your input with this important task and invites you to participate in this process by:

- 

Completing an online Community Profile Survey that will be available the week of August 26.  The Survey will be available in English, Spanish, Chinese, Hindi, and Korean.

- 

Attending one of three Community Forums that are tentatively scheduled for the weeks of September 6 and 13. 

Directions to access and complete the online Survey and the dates, times, and locations of the Community Forums will be provided the week of August 19. Ongoing information regarding the process will be posted on the District website.

Additionally, Focus Groups will be scheduled with specific individuals and organizations within the District to provide input to the desired characteristic.  

To assist the Board with this important process, we have retained the services of Hazard, Young, Attea & Associates (HYA), a consulting firm that specializes in assisting School Boards with the selection of superintendents, and who assisted the District with the superintendent selection in 2017.  HYA will present the results of the Survey, Community Forums, and Focus Groups along with a List of Desired Characteristics at the Board meeting of October 10.

If you have any questions regarding the process, please feel free to contact me at mary\_jo\_carreon@pleasantonusd.net.  Thank you in advance for your assistance with this most important task.​Sincerely,  ![](https://s3.amazonaws.com/ps-feeds-production/inline_images_1723506664333-Mary+Jo+Carreon+eSignature+2023.jpg)​Mary Jo Carreon President, Board of Trustees 


To see the post in ParentSquare, please visit the following link: https://www.mystudentsquare.com/feeds/34883427?s=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJ1c2VyX2lkIjoxMTgxOTIxNywiZXhwIjoxNzMxNDU1NTU4LCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5teXN0dWRlbnRzcXVhcmUuY29tL2ZlZWRzLzM0ODgzNDI3IiwibWV0aG9kIjoiR0VUIiwicXVlcnkiOnt9LCJyZXF1ZXN0Ijp7fX0.XyS30e6a0HZximqwI4spt2JKWk9BsFXXwP8r3ZUFBSo

parts.body:
tsbhydra79@gmail.com
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=tsbhydra79%40gmail.com&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fpolicies.google.com%2Fterms%2Fupdate%3Futm_source%3Dtos2024-email%26utm_medium%3Demail>

We’re updating our Terms of Service on May 22, 2024, so we wanted to let
you know ahead of time.

These changes won’t affect the way you use our services
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=tsbhydra79%40gmail.com&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fpolicies.google.com%2Fterms%2Fservice-specific%3Futm_source%3Dtos2024-email%26utm_medium%3Demail>,
but they should help make it easier for you to understand what to expect
from Google — and what we expect from you — as you use our services.

You can see the new terms here
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=tsbhydra79%40gmail.com&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fpolicies.google.com%2Fterms%2Fupdate%3Futm_source%3Dtos2024-email%26utm_medium%3Demail>.
We also summarized the changes at the bottom of this email.

*What do I need to do?*

    - *If you’re under the age required to manage your own Google Account
     
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=tsbhydra79%40gmail.com&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.google.com%2Faccounts%2Fanswer%2F1350409%3Futm_source%3Dtos2024-email%26utm_medium%3Demail>:*
       - We sent this email to your parent or guardian so that they can help
       you understand our updates better.
       - Please discuss this email with your parent or guardian to decide if
       you need to do anything different with your account.
    - * If you’re a parent or guardian, and you allow your child to use the
    services:*
       - Please review the updates to our terms with your child and help
       them decide whether they need to make any changes to their account.
       - Please remember that these terms apply to you and you’re
       responsible for your child’s activity on the services.
    - *If you’re the administrator of a Google Workspace corporate or
    educational account and you’ve enabled your users to access Google
    Additional Services
     
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=tsbhydra79%40gmail.com&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.google.com%2Fa%2Fanswer%2F181865%3Futm_source%3Dtos2024-email%26utm_medium%3Demail>:
    *
       - Our new Terms of Service won’t affect the Google Workspace
       agreement between Google and your organization. These new terms will  
only
       apply to those users to whom you’ve given access to Google Additional
       Services
        
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=tsbhydra79%40gmail.com&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.google.com%2Fa%2Fanswer%2F181865%3Futm_source%3Dtos2024-email%26utm_medium%3Demail>.
       You can always manage whether your users have access to Google  
Additional
       Services, and which ones, in your Admin console.
    - *If you’re a Google Workspace reseller whose customers have enabled
    their users to access Google Additional Services
     
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=tsbhydra79%40gmail.com&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.google.com%2Fa%2Fanswer%2F181865%3Futm_source%3Dtos2024-email%26utm_medium%3Demail>:*
       - Our new Terms of Service won’t affect your Google Workspace
       agreement with your customers. These new terms will only apply to your
       customers’ users who’ve been given access to Google Additional
       Services
        
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=tsbhydra79%40gmail.com&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.google.com%2Fa%2Fanswer%2F181865%3Futm_source%3Dtos2024-email%26utm_medium%3Demail>.
       Your customers can always manage whether their users have access to  
Google
       Additional Services, and which ones, in their Admin console.
    - *If you’re any other user of the services
     
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=tsbhydra79%40gmail.com&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fpolicies.google.com%2Fterms%2Fservice-specific%3Futm_source%3Dtos2024-email%26utm_medium%3Demail>:
    *
       - Please read this email to understand our updated terms and your
       options for further action.
       - If you agree to the new terms, no further action is needed.

*What’s changing?*

You can review the new Google Terms of Service here
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=tsbhydra79%40gmail.com&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fpolicies.google.com%2Fterms%2Fupdate%3Futm_source%3Dtos2024-email%26utm_medium%3Demail>.
At a glance, here’s what this update covers:

    - *Generative AI terms.* We’re moving our existing Generative AI
    Additional Terms
     
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=tsbhydra79%40gmail.com&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fpolicies.google.com%2Fterms%2Fgenerative-ai%3Futm_source%3Dtos2024-email%26utm_medium%3Demail>
    to our main Terms of Service and adding other AI-related clarifications.
    For example – we won’t claim ownership over original content generated by
    our AI-powered services.
    - *More clarity on abusive activity.* We’re providing more examples and
    details about abuse and interference with our services that isn’t  
allowed.
    - *More details on limitations of liability.* For users outside the US,
    we’re adding clarifications to our limitations of liability and indemnity
    sections to avoid any misunderstandings in light of local laws or  
customs.
    - *More clarity on disputes.* We’re clarifying that if you violate our
    terms, our remedies aren’t limited to suspension or termination of your
    access to the services, but may include other remedies under applicable
    law. If problems or disputes arise between us about these terms, you’ll
    have the opportunity to describe the issues and address them.
    - *Updates to reflect how our services work.* We’re adding language
    about how our services work, and updating certain Google service brand
    names that have changed over time.
    - *For users based in the European Economic Area (EEA) only:*
       - In addition to the changes described above, we’re adding more
       explanatory text to help you understand the legal concept of  
“guarantees”
       under EU and local law.
       - For more details, please see this summary of key changes to the EEA
       versions of our Terms
        
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=tsbhydra79%40gmail.com&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fpolicies.google.com%2Fterms%2Fchanges%3Futm_source%3Dtos2024-email%26utm_medium%3Demail>
       .

If you don’t agree to the new terms, you should remove your content
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=tsbhydra79%40gmail.com&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fpolicies.google.com%2Fterms%2Fdefinitions%23toc-terms-your-content%3Futm_source%3Dtos2024-email%26utm_medium%3Demail>
and stop using the services. You can also end your relationship with us at
any time, without penalty, by closing your Google Account
<https://accounts.google.com/AccountChooser?Email=tsbhydra79%40gmail.com&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.google.com%2Faccounts%2Fanswer%2F32046%3Futm_source%3Dtos2024-email%26utm_medium%3Demail>
.

Thank you for using Google services!


© 2024 Google LLC 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043
You have received this email to update you about important changes to
Google’s Terms of Service.

tsbhydra79@gmail.com

We’re updating our Terms of Service on May 22, 2024, so we wanted to let you know ahead of time.

These changes won’t affect the way you use our services, but they should help make it easier for you to understand what to expect from Google — and what we expect from you — as you use our services.

You can see the new terms here. We also summarized the changes at the bottom of this email.

What do I need to do?

  • If you’re under the age required to manage your own Google Account:
    • We sent this email to your parent or guardian so that they can help you understand our updates better.
    • Please discuss this email with your parent or guardian to decide if you need to do anything different with your account.
  • If you’re a parent or guardian, and you allow your child to use the services:
    • Please review the updates to our terms with your child and help them decide whether they need to make any changes to their account.
    • Please remember that these terms apply to you and you’re responsible for your child’s activity on the services.
  • If you’re the administrator of a Google Workspace corporate or educational account and you’ve enabled your users to access Google Additional Services:
    • Our new Terms of Service won’t affect the Google Workspace agreement between Google and your organization. These new terms will only apply to those users to whom you’ve given access to Google Additional Services. You can always manage whether your users have access to Google Additional Services, and which ones, in your Admin console.
  • If you’re a Google Workspace reseller whose customers have enabled their users to access Google Additional Services:
    • Our new Terms of Service won’t affect your Google Workspace agreement with your customers. These new terms will only apply to your customers’ users who’ve been given access to Google Additional Services. Your customers can always manage whether their users have access to Google Additional Services, and which ones, in their Admin console.
  • If you’re any other user of the services:
    • Please read this email to understand our updated terms and your options for further action.
    • If you agree to the new terms, no further action is needed.

What’s changing?

You can review the new Google Terms of Service here. At a glance, here’s what this update covers:

  • Generative AI terms. We’re moving our existing Generative AI Additional Terms to our main Terms of Service and adding other AI-related clarifications. For example – we won’t claim ownership over original content generated by our AI-powered services.
  • More clarity on abusive activity. We’re providing more examples and details about abuse and interference with our services that isn’t allowed.
  • More details on limitations of liability. For users outside the US, we’re adding clarifications to our limitations of liability and indemnity sections to avoid any misunderstandings in light of local laws or customs.
  • More clarity on disputes. We’re clarifying that if you violate our terms, our remedies aren’t limited to suspension or termination of your access to the services, but may include other remedies under applicable law. If problems or disputes arise between us about these terms, you’ll have the opportunity to describe the issues and address them.
  • Updates to reflect how our services work. We’re adding language about how our services work, and updating certain Google service brand names that have changed over time.
  • For users based in the European Economic Area (EEA) only:
    • In addition to the changes described above, we’re adding more explanatory text to help you understand the legal concept of “guarantees” under EU and local law.
    • For more details, please see this summary of key changes to the EEA versions of our Terms.

If you don’t agree to the new terms, you should remove your content and stop using the services. You can also end your relationship with us at any time, without penalty, by closing your Google Account.

Thank you for using Google services!

© 2024 Google LLC 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043

Hey!

We wanted to let you know that we’re updating our Terms of Service, Privacy Policy, Paid Services Terms, and Community Guidelines. We periodically make these updates as our business evolves or to respond to new laws.

These changes will take effect on April 15, 2024.

Here are some highlights of what we’ve updated:

  • How we describe our services: Made it easier to understand how Discord works, the features we offer, and how our services can be personalized for you.
  • How we resolve disputes: Updated our informal dispute resolution process and our arbitration agreement. We work hard to make sure you always love Discord and hope there’s never a dispute!
  • How we approach privacy: Provided more information about privacy rights and how they are exercised. We also updated what data we collect and how we use it. Your privacy is important to us, and we try to limit what information we collect and give you control over your privacy on Discord.
  • How we explain our Community Guidelines: Added more context and made our guidelines easier to understand.

We encourage you to read the updated documents in full. We’ve also summarised important changes on our blog.

Thanks for helping us make Discord the best place for people to hang out and talk together!

Discord

headers.Subject: Update your username by March 4, 2024

parts.body:
Hello Hydra,

We’re asking everyone to choose a unique username instead of using discriminators in their username (username0000). Starting **March 4, 2024**, Discord will begin assigning usernames to users who have not chosen one themselves. You are receiving this email because you have not chosen a new username.

This is a notice that if you do not update your username by **March 4, 2024**, Discord will assign a new, unique username to your account. We will try to assign you a unique username that is similar to your current username. 

You can update your username now by following these instructions:

**On Desktop/Browser** 

1. Select the **cog wheel** in the bottom left to open User Settings: https://click.discord.com/ls/click?upn=qDOo8cnwIoKzt0aLL1cBeI2UA2j89-2FlL1B4wEeG0PVKjI70qpZcDuih8y3IVB2MmZlXu_zLhQin4QQBUKBu1DN1ckDpNCCtYdGXGF-2BNBKhyYDdgFnqq6cz6LpH-2BdHz2ERPlX651cfCyRzyeEx1ZVyzeGZNWIpFbReabGloCOMnD8LhO-2FYh6PogNq3PuASYQdNB-2FiKLAlhWtrdyqQg9I2zB5brgKH-2BA8WzfXrFa7CYuJHyLXHuSEpB51sWJqi2-2Bz6NN1tDI0UXFcwYnp4aT4fmh3nxglfqx2UfuJtcHC2rDfnw-2BkhiF0pLdS2sckjZgeYMnB0B

**On Mobile**
